new_version_errors.1.2.2:
The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '1.2.2' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/APAV-{{ version }}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "apav" %}
{% set version = "1.3.1" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/APAV-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d23c6f4c4d5cd688604a44777a03fb8b8b67bc8a9f3af6259d41d1d86f2300b5

build:
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  script_env:
    - QT_QPA_PLATFORM=offscreen

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - libgomp      # [linux]
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - poetry
    - cython
  run:
    - fast-histogram
    - lmfit >=1.0
    - numba
    - numpy >=1.17
    - periodictable
    - pyqt >=5.11
    - pyqtgraph >=0.11.0
    - pytest >=5
    - pytest-qt >=3
    - python
    - tabulate

test:
  imports:
    - apav
    - apav.analysis
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://gitlab.com/jesseds/apav
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'APAV: Python analysis for atom probe tomography'
  description: |
    APAV (Atom Probe Analysis and Visualization) is a Python library 
    for the analysis and visualization of atom probe tomography 
    experiments
  doc_url: https://apav.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  dev_url: https://gitlab.com/jesseds/apav

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jan-janssen
